tags.scm query files in this directory are vendored from the aider project:

  https://github.com/Aider-AI/aider  (aider/queries/tree-sitter-language-pack/
  and aider/queries/tree-sitter-languages/), fetched 2026-06-05 from branch main.

aider is licensed under the Apache License 2.0:
  https://github.com/Aider-AI/aider/blob/main/LICENSE.txt

Files: c, cpp, dart, go, java, javascript, kotlin, php, ruby, rust, scala,
swift, typescript (one <lang>-tags.scm each).

Local modifications (recorded R3 deviations):
- typescript-tags.scm: appended const/let arrow-function and function-expression
  captures (copied from javascript-tags.scm patterns) — upstream lacks them and
  `const X = () =>` is the dominant React/TS declaration style.
- tsx files reuse typescript-tags.scm (no separate tsx query upstream; the tsx
  grammar is a TypeScript superset).
- Objective-C (.m/.mm): no upstream query — files stay on the generic regex
  fallback by design.
